Approach

-   Base Case:

    -   If root is null, return null (no ancestor found).
    -   If root matches p or q, return root (found one of the target nodes).

-   Recursive Traversal:

    -   Recursively search in the left and right subtrees.
    -   If both left and right return non-null values, root is the Lowest Common Ancestor.
    -   If only one subtree returns a non-null value, return that non-null value.

-   Final Result:

The function returns the node where p and q diverge in the tree.